pageTitle: Johnson named fair board president | LaRueCountyHerald.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {27278=The LaRue County Herald News | circulation@laruecountyherald.com | 270-358-3118 40 Shawnee Drive, Hodgenville, KY 42748 Office Hours are 8:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Monday through Friday, 34470=Copyright © 2015, 21742=The LaRue County Fair Board selected a new president, vice president and treasurer Aug. 19 after accepting letters of resignation from Terry L. Cruse and MaDonna Hornback, respectively. Steve Johnson, who was serving as vice president and is also city police chief, was elected to serve out the remainder of Cruse’s term. Bob DeVary was elected vice president; and Sandy Bell was elected to fulfill Hornback’s term.}
